The paper deals with image forensics, specifically contrast enhancement forensics, and proposes a new framework based on convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves feature extraction and classification, which are common topics in machine learning and multimedia processing, hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely. The paper deals with identifying tampered images, which falls under the category of computer security, hence cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possibility. The paper also involves image processing and analysis, which is a common topic in information retrieval, hence cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possibility. Finally, the paper involves the design of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possibility.
